{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_start","contentIndex":1,"partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to decide vote based on record. The prompt says we must rely on admitted evidence. The record is extensive showing evidence of Israel invading Syrian side of Mount Hermon, temporary defensive, but still control. The question: whether proposition is demonstrated (meaning evidence meets preponderance). As council member, we have to decide.\n\nWe need to maybe verify any evidence for opposing side, but given the record, the plaintiff argued Yes, defendant No. We need to decide based on the admitted evidence (the exhibits listed). The record includes evidence confirming entry, capture, control, statements indicating intent to stay until security arrangement. That meets the elements: location in Syria, action of military offensive (capture, takeover), intent to establish control (stay until arrangement). Even though described as temporary/defensive, that still indicates control. So we likely vote \"demonstrated\". Provide concise rationale up to three sentences.\n\nLet's craft rationale: \"The admitted evidence shows Israeli forces entered Syrian territory, captured the Syrian side of Mount Hermon, and officials stated they would remain there until a security arrangement was achieved, satisfying the elements of a military offensive intended to establish control over a portion of Syria. The sources are official statements and credible reporting, meeting the market’s authority requirements. Therefore the proposition is demonstrated.\"\n\nNow call mcp with tool aar_submit_council_vote.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-b325f40aba61935a","name":"mcp","arguments":{},"partialArgs":"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openai/gpt-oss-120b","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782773904205,"responseId":"gen-1782773904-iR15FJH8rCbXA8TA4K69"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to decide vote based on record. The prompt says we must rely on admitted evidence. The record is extensive showing evidence of Israel invading Syrian side of Mount Hermon, temporary defensive, but still control. The question: whether proposition is demonstrated (meaning evidence meets preponderance). As council member, we have to decide.\n\nWe need to maybe verify any evidence for opposing side, but given the record, the plaintiff argued Yes, defendant No. We need to decide based on the admitted evidence (the exhibits listed). The record includes evidence confirming entry, capture, control, statements indicating intent to stay until security arrangement. That meets the elements: location in Syria, action of military offensive (capture, takeover), intent to establish control (stay until arrangement). Even though described as temporary/defensive, that still indicates control. So we likely vote \"demonstrated\". Provide concise rationale up to three sentences.\n\nLet's craft rationale: \"The admitted evidence shows Israeli forces entered Syrian territory, captured the Syrian side of Mount Hermon, and officials stated they would remain there until a security arrangement was achieved, satisfying the elements of a military offensive intended to establish control over a portion of Syria. The sources are official statements and credible reporting, meeting the market’s authority requirements. Therefore the proposition is demonstrated.\"\n\nNow call mcp with tool aar_submit_council_vote.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-b325f40aba61935a","name":"mcp","arguments":{},"partialArgs":"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openai/gpt-oss-120b","usage":{"input":0,"output":0